ma</a></li>						<li role="presentation"><a class="faq-tab blank" href="#faq" aria-controls="faq" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">FAQs</a></li>				  </ul>				  <!-- Tab panes -->				  <div class="tab-content">				  																									<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="about">											<div class="dark-get-started margin-0">																																											<p><strong><em>Dressmaker’s Treasury&nbsp;</em></strong><strong>is a collection of key tools and skills which every dressmaker needs for successful work.</strong></p><p><strong>I am offering you a great instrument to help you acquire more confidence for fulfilling your creative projects!&nbsp;</strong>You will no longer have any fear of complex sophisticated garments! You will learn to work with mock-ups, make crinolines of non-standard shapes, and sew various kinds of fabric cases for petticoats to enhance the fullness of the main skirt.</p><p><strong>Our main goal at the Corset Academy&nbsp;</strong>is to teach you how to sew wedding and evening garments. And I want you to be able to sew a high-quality garment within a relatively short time.</p><p><strong>I don’t want you to spend lots of time on doing complicated calculations and making basic skirt patterns!</strong></p><p><strong>All necessary materials are included in the course:</strong></p><ul><li><h4>Patterns of four silhouette skirts in the actual size (PDF);</h4></li><li><h4>Patterns of four silhouette skirts in half the actual size for sewing mock-ups and designing new skirt models (PDF);</h4></li><li><h4>Three tables for AUTOMATIC calculation of all parameters required for cutting a trapeze-shaped skirt, a half-circle skirt, and a full-sweep skirt (HTML). These tables contain 18 tabs for calculating necessary parameters for the mentioned types of skirts, horizontal and vertical ruffles, falbalas, and the elastic waistband skirt.</h4></li><li><h4>Three tables for AUTOMATIC calculations with fixed parameters for the trapeze-shaped skirt, the half-circle skirt, and the full-sweep skirt (HTML);</h4></li></ul><h4>Fixed parameters (i.e. measurements) allow you to quickly calculate necessary data for cutting ruffles and falbalas for a skirt of a certain size: consumption of main fabric, lining fabric, decorative materials, etc.</h4><p><strong>Our new course&nbsp;<em>Dressmaker’s Treasury. Wedding Skirts and Petticoats&nbsp;</em>is a collection of important methods and skills which every dressmaker must know in order to achieve good results. It will be equally helpful for beginners and for experienced professionals!</strong></p><p><strong>Every professional dressmaker knows that sewing complex wedding skirts&nbsp;</strong>is not just about sewing together kilometers of fabric. The key thing is correct calculations and your ability to “foresee” the final results and related fabric consumption well before you start cutting and sewing.</p><p>I would also like to emphasize that the skirt from this course is merely a foundation for your own masterpieces. Let your creativity bloom!</p><p><strong>The course&nbsp;is&nbsp;useful both to beginner dressmakers, as well as experienced professionals.</strong></p><p><strong>Enjoy it!</strong></p><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;6h 12m</p>												</div>						</div>										<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript">						<div class="overlay"></div>						<!-- BEGIN Schema.org microdata added by the Add-Meta-Tags WordPress plugin --><!-- Scope BEGIN: Article --><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><!-- Scope BEGIN: Organization --><span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"><!-- Scope BEGIN: ImageObject --><span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"></span> <!-- Scope END: ImageObject --><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"></span> <!-- Scope END: Organization --><!-- Scope BEGIN: Person --><span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"><!-- Scope BEGIN: ImageObject --><span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"></span> <!-- Scope END: ImageObject --><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"></span> <!-- Scope END: Person --><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-48-conclusion/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-48-conclusion/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-05-08T19:10:19+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-05-08T19:11:01+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 48. Conclusion."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 48. Conclusion."><meta itemprop="description" content="We have reached the final pages of Dressmaker’s Treasury. Wedding Skirts and Petticoats. It is time to make a summary of what we have learnt."><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Skirts and Petticoats. Practical Part."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding skirts and petticoats. practical part., video"><!-- Scope BEGIN: ImageObject --><span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"></span> <!-- Scope END: ImageObject --><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 48. Conclusion.</h1><p>My dear dressmaker!</p><p>We have reached the final pages of <em>Dressmaker’s Treasury. Wedding Skirts and Petticoats. </em>It is time to make a summary of what we have learnt.</p><p><strong>The goal of this course was not just to teach you what to do in some or other particular case and situation, but rather to equip you with a powerful multi-functional tool!</strong> A tool which would make work on wedding skirts and their inner constructions easier and spare you a lot of time! It is quite natural if you feel like certain cases have been left behind: it is impossible to embrace everything within the framework of a single course and provide you with a scope of all existing solutions for the rest of your life. <strong>But the knowledge you have received will allow you to get things clear with basically any garment you may come across in your practical experience! </strong></p><p><strong>Remember the rules of making mock-ups, create a half-scale mock-up of your skirt first, and then scale the pattern up to the full size. </strong>I assure you that the quality of your garments will improve significantly if you use the suggested methods of working with mock-ups. They will also help you save many hours of work and spare your nerves from continuous re-working.</p><p><strong>Feel free to use the automatic calculation tables, apply them as widely as you can! </strong>There seem to be more opportunities to them than I even know myself.</p><p><strong>I hope I don’t have to convince you to buy or make a half-scale dress-form for your mock-ups. </strong>I have been demonstrating the benefits of working with this excellent tool during the whole course.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Dressmaker_Essential_Skirts/Transcripts/Tutorial%2048.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>In conclusion, let me wish you all the best things, good-natured and understanding clients, profitable and worthwhile orders! I believe in your success! </strong></p><p>You were with Tatiana Kozorovitsky. Until next time at the Corset Academy!</p></div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody --></div> <!-- Scope END: Article --><!-- END Schema.org microdata added by the Add-Meta-Tags WordPress plugin --> 					</div>															<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern">						<h3>Automatic&nbsp;Calculation Tables of All Parameters Required:</h3><p><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Dressmaker_Essential_Skirts/Tables/sun/index.htm" target="_blank">Trapeze-Shaped Skirt</a></strong></p><p><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Dressmaker_Essential_Skirts/Tables/halfSun/index.htm" target="_blank">Half-Circle Skirt</a></strong></p><p><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Dressmaker_Essential_Skirts/Tables/dlina/index.htm" target="_blank">Full-Sweep Skirt</a> </strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3>Automatic&nbsp;Calculation&nbsp;Tables with Fixed Parameters:</h3><p><strong><a href="https://corsetacadem